http://www.mercurynews.com/news/ci_6022026&cid San Jose Mercury News - Timberlake launches label in joint venture with Interscope san jose / valley start / stop paper (From the last 24 hours) Prosecutors: Aptos woman lived high life on &#36;1.5 million stolen... ACLU targets planner of so-called CIA torture flights Kawakami: Bryant reveals a tortured soul Spector defense targets forensic errors Rivals Steve Jobs, Bill Gates talk like old pals Timberlake launches label in joint venture with Interscope Article Launched: 05/30/2007 03:44:17 PM PDT LOS ANGELES- Justin Timberlake has conquered the music charts and box office. Now the superstar is aiming to turn himself into a starmaker. The pop singer will sign artists and release their music through a new record label that's a joint venture with Universal Music Group's Interscope Geffen A&M label group. "We are all excited about the talent we have to offer already on our roster, and I cannot wait to introduce the world to my new discoveries," Timberlake said in a statement issued Monday. Timberlake will serve as chairman and chief executive of the new label, dubbed Tennman Records, which will be based in Los Angeles and distributed globally by Interscope. Financial terms of the deal were not disclosed. Day-to-day operations will be handled by Ken Komisar, a former vice president at Sony BMG Music Entertainment, who was named president at Tennman. Timberlake's first two solo albums&mdash;2002's "Justified" and last year's "FutureSex/LoveSounds"&mdash;have sold more than 13 million copies combined. The Mercury News is pleased to let readers post comments about an article at the end of the article. Please increase the credibility of your post by including your full name and city when commenting. Google, EMI deal gives YouTube users access to music label's videos, clips Thieves posing as utility workers targeting San Jose seniors Ex-San Jose medical manager pleads guilty to stealing personal data Mid-70s temperatures, light