http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/5i-0&fd=R&url=http://www.eontarionow.com/entertainment/2007/06/04/will-tony-soprano-get-whacked-next-week/&cid=1116884258&ei=h4BkRteEHIL0rQO9rMChBg Will Tony Soprano get whacked next week? - EON Will Tony Soprano get whacked next week? Posted by admin in (Monday June 4, 2007 at New York Boss Phil and Jersey boss Tony stepped up their war, and put a hit on each other. Phil also puts a hit on Syl and Bobby." align="right" />Toronto - With only one episode remaining of The Sopranos, last night the writers left us with a cliffhanger. New York Boss Phil and Jersey boss Tony stepped up their war, and put a hit on each other. Phil also puts a hit on Syl and Bobby. The show started with Syl whacking one of Phil&#8217;s stooges, then Tony talking with his FBI &#8220;friend&#8221; who tells Tony New York has ordered the hits. Tony hires outside help to whack Phil, but the hitman killed the wrong guy and Tony realizes he has to go into hiding. Dr. Melfi, meanwhile, is at a dinner party at her psychiatrist&#8217;s home, and he violates her confidences and mentions at a table full of colleagues that she has a gangster patient. One of the other dinner guests quickly guesses it is Tony Soprano. Melfi, at the urging of Elliot, (her shrink) reads a recent study about sociopaths not being helped by talk therapy. In fact, the article says the sociopath manipulates a shrink and validates his behavior. So after she reads this study, Tony comes to her office and starts talking about his problems, and she is cold, sarcastic and judgmental. She finally tells him therapy is over. Tony is baffled by this abrupt decision, especially since he is in crisis with his son A.J., who is still suffering from depression. I was very disappointed in how the writers handled this segment. After 8 or 9 years of watching Dr. Melfi, this is not the way she would end therapy with a patient, even Tony. However&#8230; The writers of this show are so good, I bet she&#8217;s back next week with a better explanation. It was just too abrupt. Back to the show, though. Tony&#8217;s brother-in-law Bobby is shot and killed while shopping for electric trains. Tony goes home and tells Carm she needs to take the kids and go someplace safe for a few days. When Tony told Carm Bobby was dead, Carm didn&#8217;t even come close to crying, which is out of character for her character. Think back to anytime she heard someone was killed and she was always the first to scream and/or cry. And yet Bobby was her brother-in-law and she had no reaction to being told he was dead. Too strange. While Tony is with Carm, Patsy and Sylvio are shot. Patsy runs away, but Syl is left for dead by the hitman. Syl is in the hospital in a coma and not expected to wake up. Carm and Meadow stop by to see Janice, (where was A.J.?) and Tony and Paulie along with Tony&#8217;s driver and another guy go to a safe house. It ended with Tony lying down in bed with the gun Bobby gave him in the first episode of this season. The camera did a visceral move, as if trying to make you think someone was closing in on Tony. Will Tony get whacked next week? Will Paulie betray Tony? Will the Arabs Tony turned in to the FBI turn out to be terrorists and Tony will save us from them? Will Dr. Melfi be back? Will Syl live? Will A.J. die? 1 comment for Will Tony Soprano get whacked next week? Tony will go to use that gun that Bobby gave him and for some reason it will not work. Bobby was incompetant and the gun thou given as agift will fail Tony just as Bobby failed the Soprano Family! Comment by D.A> Savage &#8212; June 4, 2007 @ Please note that all comments are moderated. Your comment will be published if it is approved (required but not published) feed for comments on this post. Angelina Jolie Down To 100lbs U.S. Rep. William Jefferson Indicted Boeing 737 Makes Emergency Landing In Oakland Charges Dropped Against Canadian At Guantanamo Military Recruitment Up In Canada China Reveals New C