Hilton slipped into the ladies room. When she re-emerged the cat-and-mouse game with the press started again. While still on her cell, Hilton dispatched one of her assistants to fetch her a glass of some clear liquid from the bar. But hereâs the trip part. When the girl returned, Hilton actually made her hold the glass while she took sporadic sips out of it. Thatâs the image Iâm replaying in my head as I think about Hilton sitting in a 12-by-8 county jail cell in Lynwood, Calif. where sheâll have no cell or no one to hold her drink. How will she deal? Iâd like to feel sorry for her, but you know what? Sheâs in jail for willingly violating the terms of her probation. Itâs not like she was wrongly accused of a crime she didnât commit. Plus, we need a break from her. She has consistently flaunted her wealth, her dogs, her numerous fiancÃ©es and her various hair extensions in our faces for far too long. But weâre going to have to wait on that break. Unfortunately, Hiltonâs fame will likely increase tenfold now that sheâs serving time. Paris Hilton checks into L.A. County jailÂ Â  Jail bad? It's just more publicity for Paris iPredict: Paris will not serve her entire sentence Access: Paris gave sneaky details to Walters Access photo gallery: Mug shot mania Inmates already angry at Paris Sheriff wonât allow TV interviews Regardless of the length of her sentence â 45 or 23 days â weâll be inundated with daily updates on Hiltonâs life behind bars. What she had to eat, how she looks in orange (the color of her jumpsuit), who came to visit and who didnât come to visit. Plus, you know that despite all the measures in place to ensure her privacy, someone is going to get a cell phone photo of the heiress and sell it for thousands of dollars. CONTINUED: Lessons to learn MORE FROM CELEBRITY NEWS Jail bad? Itâs just another way to get publicity Paris Hilton completes first night in county jail Will Paris learn her lesson? Letâs hope so Jail bad?