http://www.allheadlinenews.com/articles/7007541337&cid AHN | "Transformers" Movie To Premiere A Day Earlier Than Expected | June 4, 2007 global news for the digital world "Transformers" Movie To Premiere A Day Earlier Than Expected June 4, 2007 12:13 p.m. EST Mary K. Brunskill - AHN News Writer Los Angeles, CA (AHN) - Paramount/Dreamworks has announced "Transformers," an upcoming movie directed by Michael Bay and executive produced by Steven Spielberg, will be opening earlier than planned. Although the film was initially slated to open July 4, it will now be in wide release July 3, with special screenings in select theaters on July 2. "Transformers" is based around the robot toy line launched by Hasbro in 1984. The toy line was centered around two groups of robots, each of which had its own leader: Optimus Prime, who believes in the sanctity of life, and Megatron, who believes in survival of the fittest and is out to destroy biological life. The upcoming film, written by Alex Kurtzman and Roberto Orci, is a live-action movie featuring Shia LeBeouf, Josh Duhamel, Tyrese Gibson and Megan Fox. Peter Cullen plays Optimus Prime and Hugo Weaving plays Megatron. After the Transformers toys came out in the '80s, a Marvel comic book series, an animated television series and a feature-length movie followed. The first Transformers film was titled "The Transformers: The Movie." Copyright © AHN Media Corp - All rights reserved. Redistribution, republication. syndication, rewriting or broadcast is expressly prohibited without the prior written consent of AHN. © 2007 by AHN Media Corp.
