http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/3-0&fd=R&url=http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/showbiz/article-23399237-details/Posh%2Band%2BCameron%2BDiaz%25C2%2592s%2Bembarrassing%2Bfashion%2Bdouble%2Bup/article.do&cid=1116948035&ei=h4BkRteEHIL0rQO9rMChBg Posh and Cameron Diazs embarrassing fashion double up | Showbiz | This is London Exhausting, senses-stretching and exhilarating A flighty fairytale alchemised into something that actually matters - superlative stuff It has its funny moments, but they are all too few It was an awesome gig at the Barbican, the atmosphere was electric Absolutely brilliant: the cast were great, the scenery was good, I laughed and cried Fiddler on the Roof A truly wonderful meal with the best waiter service I have ever experienced Posh and Cameron Diazs embarrassing fashion double up With the eyes of the showbiz world on them, Victoria Beckham and Cameron Diaz were desperate to avoid that dreaded event, the clash of outfits. So both no doubt breathed a sigh of relief when they arrived on the red carpet for a Hollywood awards ceremony. A quick glance from each confirmed that, while the former Spice Girl had opted for a zebra-print frock, the movie star was in an all-black mini dress with black spots. Then they looked down - and their smiling faces turned to thunder. Scroll down for more Posh came to grips with her new Hollywood friend Cameron Diaz during her first high profile appearance in America Snap! The stars chat about their matching shoes Both women had gone for exactly the same shoes - shiny silver high heels costing £350 with the unmistakable Christian Louboutin signature, the red undersole. Miss Diaz, 34, looked distinctly unimpressed by the coincidence as the couple chatted backstage at the MTV Movie Awards. But 33-year-old Mrs Beckham carried on regardless, tottering on stage beside the actor, Chris Tucker, and receiving a surprisingly warm welcome from the live studio audience. Scroll down for more On the prowl: Posh worked her thigh baring zebra dress while on the red carpet In the five months since her husband David announced his £128 million move from Real Madrid to the LA Galaxy football club, the mother of three has been waiting patiently for her big break. While cynics are still questioning her ability to become a bona fide star in America, her appointment as a guest presenter at the awards was a step in the right direction since it placed her among such A-list company as Miss Diaz, John Travolta, Robin Williams and Samuel L. Jackson. Scroll down for more... Victoria Beckham presented an award with actor Chris Tucker, while Johnny Depp was the night's big winner Jack Nicholson, Sacha Baron Cohen and troubled socialite Paris Hilton were also all in attendance at the star-studded event. At the awards, it was Captain Jack Sparrow who was the big winner at the awards as Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest was named best movie and its star, Johnny Depp, won for best performance. Depp joined Pirates producer Jerry Bruckheimer to accept the Golden Popcorn trophy. Scroll down for more... Paris Hilton, hours before entering jail, put on a brave face while on the red carpet. Jessica Alba prepared for a Borat style 'high five!' Bruckheimer said: "This is the man who did it all right here, Johnny Depp. Without him, we wouldn't be here." "I'd like to thank this man and Disney for not firing me first," Depp quipped. Other big winners during the live broadcast from the Gibson Amphitheater included Mike Myers, who won the MTV Generation Award, and Sacha Baron Cohen, who collected two trophies. Scroll down for more... Justin Timberlake's current love interest Jessica Beil, and his ex Cameron Diaz managed to avoid an awkward encounter on the red carpet Cohen earned the comedic performance prize for his starring turn in Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan. "Unfortunately, Borat can't be here tonight," he joked. "He's been feeling the pressures of fame and had to check himself into rehab." Cohen also claimed best-kiss honors for his smooch with Will Ferrell in Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby. Scroll down for more Amy Winehouse arrived with her husband Blake Fielder-Civil, while singer Rihanna turned heads in a plunging full-length gown The two comedians shared a long, passionate kiss - culminating in a roll-around-on-the-floor makeout session - as they accepted their awards. The movie prizes were almost upstaged by a star who wasn't nominated for any: Paris Hilton. The heiress, who has started her jail term just hours after appearing at the event, caused a commotion when she arrived on the ruby carpet outside the amphitheater. Wearing a ruffled black dress and dazzling jewels, she flashed her trademark coy smile as she posed for photos and talked with reporters. Scroll down for more Rihanna wowed the crowd with a performance of her hit Umbrella "I'm really scared but I'm ready to face my sentence," she said. "Even though this is a really hard time, I have my family, my friends and my fans to support me, and that's really helpful." Host Sarah Silverman cracked a crude joke at Hilton's expense to open the show. When the camera panned to Hilton, she was not smiling. Then the focus turned to films. MTV's irreverent mix of honors includes prizes for best fight and best villain, plus awards for aspiring filmmakers. Scroll down for more Amy Winehouse took to the stage to rock her chart topping hit Rehab Jack Nicholson was the winning villain, capturing the Golden Popcorn trophy for his mobster role in The Departed. The fight prize went to Gerard Butler, who battled The Uber Immortal in the epic 300. The breakthrough performance prize went to 9-year-old Jaden Smith, who starred opposite his father, Will Smith, in The Pursuit of Happyness. Scroll down for more... Funny men: Sacha Baron Cohen, Robin Williams and Mike Myers bonded at the event He accepted his award by video from Toronto with his dad by his side and his mom behind the camera. The two-hour program was punctuated by musical performances. Rihanna and Jay-Z paired up on her new song, Umbrella, and soul songstress Amy Winehouse sang her megahit, Rehab. The 16-year-old awards show unveiled two new categories Sunday: best movie spoof and best summer movie you haven't seen yet. Andy Signore, a filmmaker from Pennsylvania, won for United 300, a hybrid spoof of 300 and United 93. Transformers, due July 3, was named the best as-yet-unseen summer film. MTV viewers voted by telephone, text message and Internet to choose the winners in all categories. List of winners of the 2007 MTV Movie Awards: Best Movie: "Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest" Performance: Johnny Depp, "Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest" Breakthrough performance: Jaden Smith, "The Pursuit of Happyness" Comedic performance: Sacha Baron Cohen, "Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan" Kiss: Will Ferrell and Sacha Baron Cohen, "Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby" Villain: Jack Nicholson, "The Departed" Fight: Gerard Butler vs. "The Uber Immortal," "300" Summer movie you haven't seen: "Transformers" mtvU best filmmaker on campus: Josh Greenbaum, University of Southern California Movie spoof: Andy Signore, "United 300" MTV Generation Award: Mike Myers Here's a sample of the latest views published. You can click to read all views that readers have sent in. As long Victoria is trying to get publicity in the States and not in the UK then I'm all for it. Go on Victoria, show America what a truly staggering talent you are. - Trevor Roll, London Your email address will not be published make text area bigger Remember me - this will save your name, location and email address for when you leave your next comment. Email me a link to these comments. Post this story to: Search This is London Search listings, reviews and articles: Lone male in the Big Brother house, Ziggy, dates all the female contes