http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/4-0&fd=R&url=http://www.gamespot.com/news/6171953.html&cid=1116959420&ei=h4BkRteEHIL0rQO9rMChBg Brash scores $400 million - PSP News at GameSpot Brash scores $400 million Upstart Hollywood-focused developer finds big-time funds for big-time adaptations; 300, Saw in the works. Posted Jun 4, 2007 1:44 pm PT , Legendary Pictures CEO Thomas Tull was shoring up $150 million in financing for a new independent video game studio, Brash Entertainment. Specializing in games "that will be licensed with major movie, book, and music titles," the fledgling company reportedly had six projects on its slate. It would appear those numbers were a bit off. Brash today announced that it has acquired $400 million in funding to bring to the interactive medium properties based on movies, television, and music. Funding for the developer comes by way of media-focused private investment firm Abry Partners. The recently formed studio reportedly has 12 projects in the pipe, with 40 licenses from five major film studios also in its portfolio. Warner Bros. Home Entertainment Group has signed as the company's worldwide distributor. Shirking the Activision/THQ model of big-business film-to-video game tie-ins, Brash will be collaborating solely with independent studios. As Brash cofounder Mitch Davis puts it, this is so the company can be "laser focused on creating high-quality games...the other aspects of our business are left to the experts--best-of-breed partners we've tapped for their specific expertise." There's been much speculation of a PC/console adaptation of , given that Tull's Legendary Pictures made the movie in the first place. In lieu of official word of the title's existence, is citing sources that confirm 300 is in development. No other details on the game emerged, but Brash brass have stated that the company will be developing for all major consoles, handhelds, and mobile devices. However, Brash did note that development had begun on Lionsgate's gross-out horror flick , as well as on upcoming children's animated films and "action-packed thrillers." &laquo; Back to Today's News to post a comment on this story! Posted Jun 4, 2007 2:10 pm PT to rate this comment peeviness Posted Jun 4, 2007 2:10 pm PT (does not meet display criteria. login to show) Better do something good with that money. Posted Jun 4, 2007 2:07 pm PT to rate this comment RaiKageRyu Posted Jun 4, 2007 2:07 pm PT (does not meet display criteria. login to show) Posted Jun 4, 2007 2:02 pm PT to rate this comment diablobasher Posted Jun 4, 2007 2:02 pm PT (does not meet display criteria. login to show) Pretty intense. Stupid amount of money for such virtual thing. Posted Jun 4, 2007 1:57 pm PT to rate this comment DrMario57 Posted Jun 4, 2007 1:57 pm PT (does not meet display criteria. login to show) 300: March to Glory Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment Add to My Games Brash scores $400 million Zelda II leads four to VC Wii outselling PS3 in Japan five-to-one Xbox Live goes anime mad Company of Heroes team pulls trigger on Smoking Gun AU Shippin' Out June 4-8: Mario, Lara, and Shrek Latest music headlines from Chicago rockers license six songs for six different TV ads for the German automaker, with VW also streaming the songs on its site. MP3.com News Breakers: U2, Kanye, Police, Prince, MCR, Lily, Fat Joe back with Police, Blige MP3.com Digital Digest: iTunes Plus, EMI on YouTube, Zune, WMG, AllofMP3 Rockers vie for sexiest vegetarian more music news &raquo; Latest TV headlines from star now one of NBC's Dania Ramirez joins cast of next season; role, superpower still secret. supernovas after next season FBI trailer will be shown more TV news &raquo; Sidebar: The GameSpot News Blog GameSpot gets World in Conflict multiplayer beta Posted Jun 1, 2007 11:04 am PT Prince of Persia movie script reviewed Posted Jun 1, 2007 10:58 am PT Harmonix donates to keep fansite running Posted May 24, 2007 7:06 pm PT Wii boxing helps pro pugilist's reha