rs Maya Polsky. A Cook County judge awarded Maya Polsky 176 million in cash and assets in October. The figure represents half of the couple's estate. Today, the judge amended the figure to nearly $184-million because previously omitted assets increased the overall value of the estate. Maya Polsky's lawyers say she was her husband's confidant and should be considered a partner in his success. If it stands, the award would be a record in Illinois. The American Academy of Matrimonial Lawyers says it knows of no bigger award nationally. Michael Polsky's attorney says he plans to appeal the ruling. Copyright 2007 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed. News from the heartland of Illinois and Iowa. Business headlines, stock prices, and financial tips. Headlines from in, around and dealing with the classroom. City By City Online News, links, and information for your community. WQAD.com covers 32 counties in eastern Iowa and western Illinois. Healthy Quad Cities June Good health for men is important at any age. There are many significant things you can do to stay healthy such as getting recommended screenings, being tobacco free, and eating a healthy diet. To find out more, click here. Take a test drive of the Dutchman Express-Extended, the Kodiak Expandable or Pilgrim Fifth Wheel from Kamper Korner. Eat Local for Less We&#39;ve worked out deals with some of our area&#39;s best restaurants to give you 1/2 off gift certificates - $50 gift certificates for only $25! But you have to be fast - there are only a limited number of gift certificates. Download the Weather Wizard Powerful weather tools, current conditions, news headlines, and more! Includes quick-tips on how to use all the features. All content &copy; Copyright 2001 - 2007 WorldNow and WQAD. All Rights Reserved. For more information on this site, please read our
